<div class="prose-content max-w-3xl">

  <h2>How to book</h2>

  <h3>By telephone</h3>
  <p>Call us on <a href="tel:{{ site.phone | replace(' ', '') }}">{{ site.phone }}</a> from 08:00, Monday to Friday. Our reception team will ask a few brief questions to help match you to the right clinician and appointment type.</p>

  <div class="bg-amber-50 border border-amber-200 rounded-lg p-4 mb-6 not-prose">
    <p class="text-sm text-neutral-dark"><strong>Note:</strong> Some services at Leven Health Centre — including the treatment room (CTAC) and phlebotomy — are provided by NHS Fife staff and must be booked via <strong>NHS Fife Reception</strong> at the health centre, not via our telephone number above. See the <a href="/about/our-team/" class="text-brand-primary underline">Our team</a> page for details.</p>
  </div>

  <h2>Types of appointment</h2>
  <p>We offer:</p>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Telephone consultations</strong> — a clinician will call you at an agreed time</li>
    <li><strong>Face-to-face appointments</strong> — at Leven Health Centre</li>
    <li><strong>On-the-day appointments</strong> — for urgent same-day needs, call us from 08:00</li>
    <li><strong>NearMe video consultations</strong> — if a clinician invites you to a video appointment, you can join at <a href="https://nhsattend.vc/scoonie-medical-practice" rel="noopener noreferrer">nhsattend.vc/scoonie-medical-practice</a>. No account or app is needed — just a smartphone, tablet, or computer with a camera.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Who will I see?</h2>
  <p>Depending on your needs, you may be offered an appointment with:</p>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>GP</strong> — for complex or ongoing health concerns</li>
    <li><strong>Nurse Practitioner or Advanced Nurse Practitioner</strong> — for many acute conditions including infections, earache, skin complaints, UTIs, and asthma/COPD flares</li>
    <li><strong>Mental Health Nurse</strong> (Seonad or Andrew) — for mental health assessment and support; bookable directly without a GP referral</li>
    <li><strong>Primary Care Nurse</strong> — for chronic disease clinics, smears, warfarin/INR management, health screening</li>
    <li><strong>Practice Pharmacist</strong> — for medication queries and clinical reviews</li>
    <li><strong>First Contact Physiotherapist</strong> — for musculoskeletal problems; bookable directly without a GP referral</li>
  </ul>
  <p>Treatment room procedures (wound care, ear irrigation, B12 injections, suture removal) and blood tests (phlebotomy) are available via <strong>NHS Fife CTAC</strong> — contact NHS Fife Reception at Leven Health Centre to book these.</p>

  <div class="bg-amber-50 border border-amber-200 rounded-lg p-4 not-prose">
    <p class="text-sm text-neutral-dark"><strong>One problem per consultation.</strong> To give every patient the time they need, please raise one problem per appointment. If you have multiple concerns, ask our reception team about a longer or additional appointment.</p>
  </div>

  <h2>Home visits</h2>
  <p>If you are unable to attend the surgery because of illness or disability, we can arrange a home visit. Please call before 11:00 to request one. Home visits are for patients who are genuinely housebound and unable to travel safely — they are not an alternative to attending in person.</p>
  <p>After 11:00, home visits can only be arranged for genuine emergencies.</p>

  <h2>Need help sooner?</h2>
  <p>Many conditions can be treated faster without a GP appointment. Consider:</p>
  <ul>
    <li><a href="/get-help/pharmacy-first/">Pharmacy First</a> — for UTIs, earache, sinusitis, sore throat, and more</li>
    <li><a href="/get-help/self-referral/">Self-referral services</a> — direct access to physiotherapy, mental health, and more</li>
  </ul>

</div>
